Annotations

A motor carrier may combine more than one policy, and use more than one method, to meet the minimum financial responsibility requirements. Shelter Ins. Co. v. Gomez, 306 Neb. 607, 947 N.W.2d 92 (2020).

Compliance with the minimum financial responsibility requirements in this section is the responsibility of the motor carrier, not the insurer. Shelter Ins. Co. v. Gomez, 306 Neb. 607, 947 N.W.2d 92 (2020).

This section does not regulate the terms and conditions of insurance policies. Shelter Ins. Co. v. Gomez, 306 Neb. 607, 947 N.W.2d 92 (2020).
